translated: Years, Ture, district doctor, Gothenburg, b. 11/4/81 in Mularp, Skaraborg. 1st son of the clergyman Magnus Å. and Hilda Sofia Cederin. Married on 14th with Hertha Enemark. Children: Sven, b. 15, dentist, Gothenburg, John, 17, studying philosophy, Gothenburg, Ebba, 21, married to civil engineer H. Egnell, Stockholm. Graduated from Mog:ex. in Skara in 1900, received a bachelor's degree in medicine from Lund in 1903, passed the medical examination in 1907 and obtained a medical license in Stockholm in 1911. Assistant in physiology at the Karolinska Institute in 1906, held various positions as assistant doctor, senior assistant doctor, and acting doctor at multiple hospitals from 1906 to 1914, district and hospital doctor in Askersund from 1914 to 1916, district doctor in Gothenburg from 1916 to 1920 and from 1926 onwards, school doctor in Gothenburg from 1916 to 1938, doctor at Mjölkdroppen from 1916 to 1920, assistant doctor at the Gibraltars care facility for the chronically ill and tuberculosis from 1920, doctor for the Gothenburg-Särö railway from 1925. Studied abroad in Copenhagen and Berlin in 1921. Retired in 1946.
